 Last year, I mentioned how I look back at myself and I’m surprised how much I’ve learned (I believe the words I used were 
just how stupid I was
). Funny thing is these lessons learned are almost never technical, and this year is no different. It’s always something new about human relations or how the way the world works, which really follows what’s really complex in this world — the people and their interactions. This ignorance removal process (à la Buffett and Munger) is what really gets me going and I have to say is one of the big drivers of my modest success. I’m looking forward to a bright 2019 loaded with more ignorance removal and hopefully sprinkled with some wisdom acquisition if I’m lucky.

